        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:45PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stonewall, or 29 miles west of Trinidad, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, penny size hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stonewall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
